1
00:00:04,822 --> 00:00:07,072
The Bhāgavatam says
in the beginning,

2
00:00:07,072 --> 00:00:14,816
“Advaya-jñān”, which we can say
means ‘one thing to know’.

3
00:00:14,927 --> 00:00:18,498
[Buddha is Kṛṣṇa]

4
00:00:18,775 --> 00:00:19,890
Guru Mahārāj is always saying,

5
00:00:19,890 --> 00:00:25,184
“The Upaniṣads say,
‘There’s one thing to be known.’”

6
00:00:25,184 --> 00:00:27,574
We have to think about this 
carefully.

7
00:00:27,574 --> 00:00:31,343
There are different ways
we can consider it.

8
00:00:31,343 --> 00:00:37,510
So what I will suggest now
is we understand,

9
00:00:37,519 --> 00:00:42,589
if Kṛṣṇa has been asserted
as the one thing to be known,

10
00:00:42,589 --> 00:00:45,585
then whatever you see,
like I’ve always said,

11
00:00:45,585 --> 00:00:48,327
whatever you see that appears
to be related or unrelated,

12
00:00:48,327 --> 00:00:53,175
it has to be connected to Kṛṣṇa.

13
00:00:53,241 --> 00:00:55,586
Itarataś cārtheṣv
[SB: 1.1.1]

14
00:00:55,586 --> 00:00:59,288
in the four nutshell ślokas
in the Bhāgavatam—

15
00:00:59,288 --> 00:01:04,272
directly and indirectly
everything must be related to Kṛṣṇa.

16
00:01:04,272 --> 00:01:07,182
So, as we learn in China,

17
00:01:07,182 --> 00:01:12,898
it’s more helpful to conceive 
of Buddha in relation to Kṛṣṇa.

18
00:01:12,898 --> 00:01:14,823
He’s an avatar of Kṛṣṇa,

19
00:01:14,823 --> 00:01:18,432
we don’t have 
to apologise for that.

20
00:01:18,432 --> 00:01:20,716
We don’t normally think of Him 
as Kṛṣṇa,

21
00:01:20,716 --> 00:01:23,613
but it’s more interesting,
if you understand—

22
00:01:23,613 --> 00:01:25,449
Buddha is Kṛṣṇa.

23
00:01:25,449 --> 00:01:28,662
And then if you think,
“Well, why did Kṛṣṇa appear like this?

24
00:01:28,662 --> 00:01:31,977
What was His purpose?
What was the …”

25
00:01:31,977 --> 00:01:33,662
And Buddha …

26
00:01:33,662 --> 00:01:37,565
Like, we know, 
Kṛṣṇa is all-attractive,

27
00:01:37,565 --> 00:01:39,753
He’s the ultimate 
beautiful conception.

28
00:01:39,753 --> 00:01:42,413
He finds Himself attracted

29
00:01:42,413 --> 00:01:46,083
seeing His reflection in a mirror,
in a jewelled column.

30
00:01:46,113 --> 00:01:49,174
Dvārakā Kṛṣṇa seeing a picture
of Vṛndāvan Kṛṣṇa.

31
00:01:49,174 --> 00:01:53,090
Kṛṣṇa is the bhuvana-sundar,

32
00:01:53,090 --> 00:01:57,380
śrutvā guṇān bhuvana-sundara 
śṛṇvatāḿ te—
[SB: 10.52.37]

33
00:01:57,380 --> 00:01:59,048
the ultimate beautiful thing.

34
00:01:59,048 --> 00:02:03,149
The aṇgam aṇganaḥ aṇganānām 
bhūṣaṇa—

35
00:02:03,149 --> 00:02:05,936
the ornament’s ornament.

36
00:02:05,936 --> 00:02:08,858
He makes the ornaments 
look beautiful.

37
00:02:08,858 --> 00:02:11,578
Normally people put ornaments
to look beautiful;

38
00:02:11,578 --> 00:02:15,180
Kṛṣṇa, He’s that.

39
00:02:15,180 --> 00:02:17,980
So then we can understand
something too

40
00:02:17,980 --> 00:02:24,350
that, how beautiful 
Buddha would be.

41
00:02:24,381 --> 00:02:29,978
We see something in the representations
of the mūrtis, but just imagine,

42
00:02:29,988 --> 00:02:33,420
Kṛṣṇa, 
how irresistibly beautiful He is,

43
00:02:33,420 --> 00:02:39,893
charming, and, like classic Kṛṣṇa, 
liar.

44
00:02:40,046 --> 00:02:43,700
Lying. Deceiving.

45
00:02:43,700 --> 00:02:46,621
Deceit for the sake of truth.

46
00:02:46,621 --> 00:02:52,193
The crooked reality.
[Laughing]

47
00:02:52,193 --> 00:02:55,308
Because He’s saying,

48
00:02:55,308 --> 00:02:58,324
“Ahiṁsā sarva bhūtāni”—
“Stop this.”

49
00:02:58,324 --> 00:02:59,460
“But in the Vedas …”

50
00:02:59,460 --> 00:03:03,573
“Oh, forget the Veda.
Don’t you think about Veda …

51
00:03:03,584 --> 00:03:07,476
Forget Veda for now.”

52
00:03:07,942 --> 00:03:09,900
That’s why once 
on the morning walk

53
00:03:09,900 --> 00:03:12,182
some man was saying,
telling Prabhupād …

54
00:03:12,182 --> 00:03:15,461
There was this man,
who would go on the walks,

55
00:03:15,461 --> 00:03:18,301
and we can learn 
something from this.

56
00:03:18,301 --> 00:03:21,220
The devotees wanted 
to strangle him,

57
00:03:21,220 --> 00:03:23,947
and Prabhupād found him 
amusing.

58
00:03:23,947 --> 00:03:25,740
Like, when we’d go 
around a corner,

59
00:03:25,740 --> 00:03:27,539
sometimes, you know …

60
00:03:27,539 --> 00:03:30,779
devotees were like,
they really wanted to get him

61
00:03:30,779 --> 00:03:34,158
because he would say things
you could think were offensive.

62
00:03:34,158 --> 00:03:38,378
But Prabhupād found him
a good sparring partner,

63
00:03:38,378 --> 00:03:40,420
the kind of things 
he would say,

64
00:03:40,420 --> 00:03:42,037
and he’d get Prabhupād upset,

65
00:03:42,037 --> 00:03:45,519
but Prabhupād would come out
and preach in a nice way.

66
00:03:45,519 --> 00:03:48,956
So once the man was saying,

67
00:03:49,002 --> 00:03:51,781
“Oh, so-and-so has written
a very wonderful book

68
00:03:51,781 --> 00:03:54,181
about Kṛṣṇa, every page.”

69
00:03:54,181 --> 00:03:56,782
“Oh?”

70
00:03:56,782 --> 00:03:59,864
And he said, “And not only that,” 
he said,

71
00:03:59,864 --> 00:04:02,937
“so beautifully he has expressed 
there

72
00:04:02,937 --> 00:04:06,975
that one should never kill 
an animal,

73
00:04:06,975 --> 00:04:09,538
even if it’s enjoined 
in the Vedas.

74
00:04:09,538 --> 00:04:11,293
Very beautifully.”

75
00:04:11,293 --> 00:04:14,601
Prabhupād said, 
“That is atheism.

76
00:04:14,617 --> 00:04:19,926
To decry the authority of Veda,
that is atheism.”

77
00:04:19,937 --> 00:04:21,296
To not accept that …

78
00:04:21,296 --> 00:04:25,926
Now Prabhupād’s defending
meat-eating according to Veda,

79
00:04:25,926 --> 00:04:30,388
which Buddha had to deceive 
them,

80
00:04:30,388 --> 00:04:33,015
like Kṛṣṇa at the Indra-yajña,

81
00:04:33,015 --> 00:04:35,811
“Forget that and follow Me.”

82
00:04:35,858 --> 00:04:38,892
So, I just need to say,

83
00:04:38,892 --> 00:04:42,956
if we embrace Him as
(as an example)

84
00:04:43,002 --> 00:04:45,415
as Kṛṣṇa appearing 
in this way,

85
00:04:45,436 --> 00:04:47,869
that will be more charming 
to us.

86
00:04:47,869 --> 00:04:52,067
If we understand that
Rāmachandra is Kṛṣṇa

87
00:04:52,081 --> 00:04:56,367
constrained by rājā-nītiḥ,

88
00:04:56,367 --> 00:04:59,407
that’ll be more charming 
to us.

89
00:04:59,407 --> 00:05:03,967
If we think
that they are disconnected

90
00:05:03,967 --> 00:05:07,726
that will not only 
not be helpful,

91
00:05:07,726 --> 00:05:12,407
it’s āpa-siddhāntic, 
it’s not correct.

92
00:05:12,407 --> 00:05:14,376
But not to go the other way, 
where,

93
00:05:14,376 --> 00:05:17,728
you know,
“God is everywhere, Swamiji.”

94
00:05:17,728 --> 00:05:20,170
You know, not like that.

95
00:05:20,170 --> 00:05:28,377
Like, “Rāma, Kṛṣṇa, Kāli, Durga—
all the same.”

96
00:05:28,377 --> 00:05:33,129
Not the kichiri or worse,

97
00:05:33,159 --> 00:05:36,039
as Gurudev 
would sometimes say “lafra”.

98
00:05:36,039 --> 00:05:38,292
Because kichiri
is two ingredients really,

99
00:05:38,292 --> 00:05:41,381
lafra—many.

100
00:05:41,535 --> 00:05:44,121
So, but … advaya-jñān,

101
00:05:44,121 --> 00:05:48,166
we go back to … Bhāgavatam says,
“There’s only one thing to be known.”

102
00:05:48,168 --> 00:05:50,539
How is this Kṛṣṇa?

103
00:05:50,539 --> 00:05:54,850
Everything I see
is on some level

104
00:05:54,654 --> 00:05:57,701
Kṛṣṇa, came from Kṛṣṇa …

105
00:05:57,701 --> 00:05:59,888
It’s either directly 
or indirectly Kṛṣṇa.

